                <head>No. 533.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Wallace</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-02-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 12, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 52.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your No. 166, of the 18th ultimo, has been
                    received. You therein present the proposition of the Government of Turkey
                    looking to the overhauling of the books of the American Bible Society at
                    Constantinople, and the fixing of a seal upon such of them as may be found
                    unobjectionable. You also inclose copies of the correspondence exchanged upon
                    the subject.</p>
                <p>The letter of the managers of the Bible House, Messrs. Dwight and Bliss, copy of
                    which accompanies your dispatch, and of whom you sought advice concerning the
                    matter, very clearly shows the objections to the proposal.</p>
                <p>Your action thereon, in addressing the minister of foreign affairs a note
                    declining to appoint a delegate for the purpose named, is approved.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
